2018年1月，宣布計劃在不久的將來在身份證件（例如護照和國民身份證）上另開男、女之外的「第三性別」選項。<ref>{{cite news|last=Yi|first=Beh-Lih|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/taiwan-lgbt/taiwan-mulls-third-gender-option-on-passports-ids-idUSL8N1O61JZ|title=Taiwan mulls third gender option on passports, IDs|date=16 January 2018|work=Reuters|accessdate=8 April 2018|archive-date=2019-03-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329120145/https://www.reuters.com/article/taiwan-lgbt/taiwan-mulls-third-gender-option-on-passports-ids-idUSL8N1O61JZ|dead-url=no}}</ref>國家發展委員會部長陳美玲於2018年11月宣布，這些計劃將於2020年生效。<ref>{{cite web|title=New national ID card will recognize trans as a third gender in Taiwan|url=https://www.gaystarnews.com/article/new-national-id-card-will-recognize-trans-as-a-third-gender-in-taiwan/|date=22 November 2018|last=Power|first=Shannon|work=Gay Star News|accessdate=2019-11-13|archive-date=2019-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190410042738/https://www.gaystarnews.com/article/new-national-id-card-will-recognize-trans-as-a-third-gender-in-taiwan/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

